       This module is portable as far as an IEEE floating proces­
       sor is present.  The IEEE floating point  format  supports
       some  special  formats  for infinity and undefined values.
       Operations with undefined values, so called  not-a-numbers
       yield  again undefined values.  This allows to distinguish
       valid and reasonable results from undefined results (divi­
       sion by zero, ln(0), etc.).  Valid numbers are either nor­
       malized or denormalized (small values beneath zero).

